text: George Airport is a airport located in South Africa. The airport was built in 1977. A Embraer ERJ 135 (registration:ZS-SJW) operated by Airlink overshot a runway and ended up on a public road. There were no deaths. George Airport won an award by the Airports Council International (ACI).
